{{EngvarB|date=September 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2015}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Will Norris | image = Will Norris 03-09-2016.jpg | image_size = | caption = Will Norris with [[Cambridge United F.C.|Cambridge United]] in 2016 | fullname = William James Norris<ref>{{cite web |title=EFL: Club list of registered players |url=https://www.efl.com/siteassets/efl-documents/efl-released-and-retained-list---2016-17.pdf |publisher=English Football League |format=PDF |page=71 |date=20 May 2017 |accessdate=6 October 2017}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1993|08|12}} | birth_place = [[Watford]], Hertfordshire, England | height = {{height|m=1.95}}<ref>{{cite news|title=Player Profile: Will Norris|url=http://www.cambridge-united.co.uk/team/player-profile/will-norris/35|publisher=Cambridge United FC|date=28 January 2016}}</ref> | position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]] | currentclub = [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] | clubnumber = 31 | youthyears1 = 2006–2011 |youthclubs1 = [[Northwood F.C.|Northwood]] | years1 = 2011 |clubs1 = [[Hatfield Town F.C.|Hatfield Town]] |caps1 = 16 |goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2011–2012 |clubs2 = [[Royston Town F.C.|Royston Town]] |caps2 = 28 |goals2 = 0 | years3 = 2012–2017 |clubs3 = [[Cambridge United F.C.|Cambridge United]] |caps3 = 84 |goals3 = 0 | years4 = 2012–2013 |clubs4 = → [[Royston Town F.C.|Royston Town]] (loan) |caps4 = 28 |goals4 = 0 | years5 = 2013 |clubs5 = → [[Royston Town F.C.|Royston Town]] (loan) |caps5 = 6 |goals5 = 0 | years6 = 2015–2016 |clubs6 = → [[Braintree Town F.C.|Braintree Town]] (loan) |caps6 = 24 |goals6 = 0 | years7 = 2017– |clubs7 = [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] |caps7 = 1 |goals7 = 0 | club-update = 15:00, 6 May 2018 (BST) }} '''William James Norris''' (born 12 August 1993) is an English professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].
==Club career== ===Royston Town=== Without a club at the start of the 2011–12 season, Norris made an approach to join Hertfordshire side [[Royston Town F.C.|Royston Town]] who in the previous season had narrowly missed out on promotion after finishing 3rd in the [[Spartan South Midlands Football League|Spartan South Midlands League Premier Division]]. He played a number of games for the reserve team where his performances caught the attention of then first team manager, Paul Attfield, who pulled him into the first team.<ref>{{cite news|title=Will Norris: How an approach to Royston led to Cambridge United chance|url=http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/Norris-approach-Royston-led-Cambridge-United/story-28616792-detail/story.html|publisher=[[Cambridge News]]|date=27 January 2016}}</ref> On 20 September 2011, he made his debut for Royston in a 4–1 home win against [[Haringey Borough F.C.|Haringey Borough]] in the Spartan South Midlands League Premier Division Cup.<ref>{{cite news|title=Match Report:Royston Town v Haringey Borough|url=http://www.roystontownfc.co.uk/match-reports/match-report-royston-town-v-haringey-borough-2/|publisher=[[Royston Town FC|roystontownfc.co.uk]]|date=20 September 2011}}</ref> Norris went on to make 41 appearances in all competitions in 2011–12 helping the club to secure the Spartan South Midlands Premier Division title and a cup double which included the Spartan South Midlands League Premier Division Cup and the South Midlands Floodlit Cup. In the quarter final of the [[Cambridgeshire Invitation Cup]] against [[Cambridge City F.C.|Cambridge City]] on 25 January 2012, the game was decided by a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]] in which Norris pulled off a number of saves in [[Sudden death (sport)|sudden death]] before scoring the winning penalty to send Royston into the semi-final.<ref>{{cite news|title=Norris heroics send Crows into semis|url=http://www.royston-crow.co.uk/sport/royston-town-fc/norris_heroics_send_crows_into_semis_1_1189960|publisher=[[Royston Crow (newspaper)|Royston Crow]]|date=27 January 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Norris the hero for Royston|url=http://www.hertfordshiremercury.co.uk/Norris-hero-Royston/story-21996134-detail/story.html|publisher=[[Hertfordshire Mercury]]|date=26 January 2012}}</ref>
===Cambridge United=== On 16 July 2012, Norris signed for Cambridge United on a two-year deal and was loaned back to Royston Town for the duration of the 2012–13 season, helping the club to a 7th-place finish in the Southern Football League Division One Central.<ref>{{cite news|title=Cambridge United sign teenage goalkeeper Will Norris|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/18860112|publisher=[[BBC Sport|bbc.co.uk]]|date=16 July 2012}}</ref>
Norris spent the first half of the season 2013–14 with Cambridge as second choice to [[Chris Maxwell (footballer)|Chris Maxwell]], before re-joining Royston in December 2013 on a short-term loan spell.<ref>{{cite news|title=Cambridge United goalkeeper Will Norris loaned to Royston|url=http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/Cambridge-United-goalkeeper-Norris-loaned-Royston-ahead-FA-Cup-showdown-Sheffield-United/story-22392060-detail/story.html|publisher=[[Cambridge News]]|date=6 December 2013}}</ref> He was recalled to make his first team debut for Cambridge in a 1–0 away win at [[Tamworth F.C.|Tamworth]] in the [[Conference Premier]] on 21 January 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=Will Norris produced a 'mature' performance in Cambridge United's win over Tamworth|url=http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/Norris-produced-amature-performance-Cambridge-Uniteds-win-Tamworth-says-Richard-Money/story-22392075-detail/story.html|publisher=[[Cambridge News]]|date=22 January 2014}}</ref> On 30 January 2014, he signed a new contract with the club which extended his previous deal by two and a half years to 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=Duo Sign New Deals|url=http://www.cambridge-united.co.uk/news/article/duosignnewdeals-1328305.aspx|publisher=Cambridge United F.C.|date=30 January 2014}}</ref> He went on to make a total of 15 league appearances helping Cambridge make a return to [[The Football League]], after a nine-year absence, via the Conference play-offs. Norris kept a clean sheet in Cambridge's 4–0 victory over Gosport Borough in the [[2014 FA Trophy Final|2013–14 FA Trophy Final.]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Will can't wait for Wembley return in FA Trophy Final|url=http://www.thefa.com/news/competitions/fa-trophy/2014/mar/final-preview-will-norris-210314|publisher=[[The FA|thefa.com]]|date=21 March 2014}}</ref>
Norris made his [[The Football League|Football League]] debut for Cambridge in a 2–2 draw at home to [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]] on 11 April 2015.<ref>{{cite news|title=Cambridge United 2–2 Accrington Stanley|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/32179941|publisher=[[BBC Sport|bbc.co.uk]]|date=11 April 2015}}</ref> He went on to make a total of 3 appearances in the league in [[2014–15 Football League Two|2014–15]] as Cambridge finished 19th in their first season back in the Football League.<ref>{{cite news|title=Will Norris taking the positives from Cambridge United's Sky Bet League Two campaign|url=http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/Norris-taking-positives-Cambridge-United-8217-s/story-26444233-detail/story.html|publisher=[[Cambridge News]]|date=6 May 2015}}</ref> At the end of the season his contract was extended to 2018, and was loaned to [[Braintree Town F.C.|Braintree Town]] for the beginning of 2015–16.<ref>{{cite news|title=Cambridge United keeper Will Norris moves to Braintree Town on loan after signing new deal|url=http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/Norris-moves-Braintree-Town-loan-signing-new/story-26843416-detail/story.html|publisher=[[Cambridge News]]|date=7 July 2015}}</ref> On 8 August 2015, he made his debut for Braintree in a 1–0 away defeat to [[Chester City F.C.|Chester City]] in the [[2015–16 National League|National League]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Chester 1–0 Braintree|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/33744769|publisher=[[BBC Sport|bbc.co.uk]]|date=8 August 2015}}</ref> After a run of impressive performances, keeping four clean sheets in six games, he was named the National League's Player of the Month for October.<ref>{{cite news|title=Braintree Keeper Takes October Player Award|url=http://www.thenationalleague.org.uk/news/details.php?news_id=16460|publisher=[[The National League|thenationalleague.org.uk]]|date=6 November 2015}}</ref> At the time of collecting the award Norris had amassed 9 clean sheets in the league; the most of any goalkeeper in the top 5 English divisions. On 9 January 2016, Norris was recalled from his loan with Braintree.<ref>{{cite news|title=Cambridge United boss Shaun Derry urges Will Norris to play for keeps|url=http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/Cambridge-United-boss-Shaun-Derry-urges-Norris/story-28497618-detail/story.html|publisher=[[Cambridge News]]|date=11 January 2016}}</ref> He went on to make a total of 21 league appearances for Cambridge, keeping 9 clean sheets, as the club finished 9th in [[2015–16 Football League Two|League Two]]. His contract was extended by a further year, to 2019.<ref>{{cite news|title=Will Norris signs new three-year Cambridge United deal|url=http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/Norris-moves-Braintree-Town-loan-signing-new/story-26843416-detail/story.html|publisher=[[Cambridge News]]|date=9 June 2016}}</ref>
In the 2016–17 season Norris saved a club record of five penalties in one season, including two in second half stoppage time against [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]].<ref name="Cambridge News">{{cite news|title=Cambridge United view from the pressbox: Will Norris is a grand keeper|url=http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/cambridge-united-view-from-the-pressbox-will-norris-is-a-grand-keeper/story-29795287-detail/story.html|publisher=[[Cambridge News]]|date=11 October 2016}}</ref> The gloves he used in the double penalty save against Accrington raised £1,000 at a [[Auction|charity auction]], with the proceeds being donated to injured footballers Shaun Whiter and Joey Abbs, who were victims of a hit-and-run incident.<ref name="Cambridge News"/>
===Wolverhampton Wanderers===
On 11 July 2017, Norris signed a three-year deal for [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] for an undisclosed fee, a day after the [[EFL Championship|Championship]] club had signed a fellow former Cambridge goalkeeper, [[John Ruddy]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Will Norris: Wolves sign Cambridge United goalkeeper for undisclosed fee |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/40567977 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=11 July 2017}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 8 August 2017 in a 1–0 win against [[Yeovil Town F.C.|Yeovil Town]] in the second round of the [[EFL Cup|Carabao Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Wolverhampton Wanderers 1–0 Yeovil Town|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/40785920|publisher=BBC Sport|date=8 August 2017}}</ref> Norris made his league debut for Wolves on 6 May 2018 against [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Sunderland 3-0 Wolves|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43938926|publisher=BBC Sport|date=6 May 2018}}</ref>
